      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Great Foundation",
          "reviewText": "I absolutely love the L.A. Girl Pro Coverage foundation! The shade Toast matches my skin tone perfectly\u2014it blends effortlessly and gives me a smooth, radiant finish without feeling heavy. It provides great coverage while still looking natural, and it lasts all day without getting cakey or patchy. I also appreciate the pump bottle, which makes it super easy to use and prevents product waste. For the price, this foundation performs better than many high-end brands. Definitely my go-to foundation from now on!",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on October 22, 2025",
          "customer": "hawthorne",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGHBIH7FAA2MSL2L7YRASYLZBWGQ",
          "customerStarsRating": 5,
          "productSpecs": {
            "color": "Toast",
            "size": "0.95 Fl Oz (Pack of 1)"
          },
          "helpfulVotes": "4 people found this helpful"
        },
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Lasted through an aerial performance which involved fake blood being poured on me!",
          "reviewText": "I\u2019m a circus performer, and I needed urgent white foundation for a show. This saved my life!! 1) This is so good. Great coverage. I did two layers and setting powder, but one layer is really good for softer less clowny looks. 2) This did NOT come off easy at all. Not only did it last through an entire aerial performance, but I got fake blood poured on me and it didn\u2019t budge one bit. It didn\u2019t even rinse off with the water in the shower until I used makeup remover. Idk what people are talking about with it coming off easily. I even wore my glasses to drive with this look for about 2 hours and less of it moved than my normal foundation. 3) It also didn\u2019t smell?? It smelled exactly how my regular foundation and concealer smell lol (and those are prestige brands) Overall really solid. I will be using again and likely purchasing again. I included before and after pics of the look. Not sure why other people are complaining, must be a skill issue lol.",
          "reviewDate": "Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2026",
          "customer": "Lily Wheaton",
          "customerProfileUrl": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/profile/amzn1.account.AGBR5E3LFGJ6ILNVCQ7DERK7HDWA",
